Privacy Policy
Last Updated and Effective: February 15, 2023
This privacy policy (the "Privacy Policy") governs the access to, use of, and applies to the information collected by, Sony Media Cloud Services LLC ("
Sony MCS
," "
we
," "
us
," or "
our
") both offline and online, including through
www.sonymcs.com
,
www.cimediacloud.com
,
app.cimediacloud.com
, as well as our services, products and related software toolset, which are presently marketed under the trademark Ci (pronounced "see") (collectively, "
Ci
") and through any interactive features, applications, widgets, blogs, social networks and other online or wireless offerings that link to this Privacy Policy, whether accessed via computer, mobile device or other technology (collectively, "
Sony MCS Properties
").
By using Ci and/or accessing the Sony MCS Properties you expressly consent to the information practices described in this Privacy Policy. Our Privacy Policy is intended to assist you in making informed decisions when using our website and services. Please take your time to read and understand the policy. In addition, please review our Terms of Service at
www.cimediacloud.com/terms
.
If you do not consent to this Privacy Policy and the Terms, you must discontinue your use of the Sony MCS Properties.
What Does This Policy Cover?
This Privacy Policy describes Sony Media Cloud Services LLC's use of your data.
As such, please note that when you enter any subsites accessible through
www.sonymcs.com
,
www.cimediacloud.com
,
app.cimediacloud.com
,
workspace.cimediacloud.com/
, or other Sony MCS Properties, such subsites may have their own specific privacy statements. Additionally, the websites of companies affiliated with Sony MCS companies, including some that are linked to/from the Sony MCS Properties, and internet domains that are linked to/from the Sony MCS Properties, may have different policies; therefore, please review the privacy policy notices on those websites if you visit them. The Sony MCS Properties are not intended for use by anyone younger than the age of 18.
Sony MCS, a company having its registered address at
16535 Via Esprillo, San Diego, CA 92127
, is the data controller. Sony MCS is responsible for and controls the processing of personal information on the Sony MCS Properties. This Privacy Policy applies only to instances where Sony MCS acts as a data controller. For additional information regarding our practices as a data controller, please refer to
Notice to EEA,UK, and Switzerland Residents
below.
This Privacy Policy does not apply when we act a data processor, including, wherever our customers use Ci to submit, upload, download, store, manage, share, process or otherwise use content files through a Ci account ("
Customer Content
"). Where required, we will contractually committed ourselves, including by signing data processing agreements, to only process such Customer Content on behalf of, and under the instruction of, the respective customer (controller). Accordingly, this Privacy Policy does
not
apply to such processing.
